post_summaries.description: The image is a portrait of themrgordo, taken by @michaelmannioncomedian at the @altogetherotherwise zineswap party. He is wearing a faded black cap, round glasses, a purple t-shirt with a design, and a pink corduroy jacket. He has long brown hair and a mustache. A silver camera hangs around his neck. He is standing in front of a shelf with orange storage bins and books.

A person with long hair, a mustache, and tattoos is standing in front of a dark, ornate door. They are wearing a black t-shirt with the words "Heavy Nettle" printed on it. The post is advertising "Heavy Nettle" t-shirts made with organic cotton and GOTS-certified inks.

The image shows a person standing on a beach, holding a large stick. The background includes dunes and tall grass. The person is wearing casual clothing and a hat. The caption mentions finding the stick and wanting to bring it home on the train, along with hashtags related to stick reviews, Northumberland, and wizard world.

The image is a black and white 35mm photograph of themrgordo standing in front of a large rock (possibly a stone circle or monument). He's wearing a t-shirt with "EARTH" printed on it, a jacket, and a hat. The caption mentions the Pennie Way, Kinder Scout, and drawing stones.

The image shows a stage setup with various guitar amplifiers (Hiwatt, Trace Elliot, Peavey) and a guitar. A neon sign that says "Dirty Otter" is prominently displayed. The post caption mentions the person designed the logo for "Dirty Otter Leeds" gig and party promoters.

The image is a close-up of a zine cover titled "Scrap Book: Martin Phillipps Notes From The Archive (volume 1)." It features handwritten notes, drawings, and a sticker of "The Chills," a band. The post mentions that the zine is a collection of drawings, notes, and bits from the late Martin Phillips of The Chills.
